<HEAD>Seven Children Injured by Explosive Device</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RICHMOND, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An explosive device injured seven
youngsters playing with it on a balcony Wednesday, authorities said.
   One child was listed in critical condition with burns and other
injuries and two were reported in serious condition.
   Police Capt. Ed Duncan said the explosive was an M-1000, a
cylindrical device, 2{ inches in diameter, with the force of a
quarter stick of dynamite.
   The blast knocked one of the youngsters off the apartment's
second-floor balcony, Contra Costa County Sheriff's deputies said.
The injured, all boys, ranged in age from 2 or 3 years old to their
teens, authorities said.
</TEXT>
