<NOTE>Eds: Members who used the BALTIMORE-dated fifth item of PM-Deaths,
moved Tuesday as a0519, are asked to use the following.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>BALTIMORE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Associated Press reported erroneously
Tuesday that Roy W. Anderson Sr., an executive with the American
Newspaper Publishers Association who died Sunday at age 63, was a
newspaper publisher.
   Anderson was a pressman with The Chicago Tribune, assistant
mechanical supervisor at The (Akron) Beacon Journal in Ohio and The
Miami Herald, business manager at The Times-Union and Knickerbocker
News in Albany, N.Y., and general manager of the Baltimore News
American.
