Charles and Princess Diana, defeated by hay fever and tonsillitis.
   She had vowed to go on Tuesday night ``even if my nose drips
like the Nile.''
   The organizers of the opera spectacular at Earl's Court indoor
arena said the singer was resting and was ``very disappointed'' at
not being able to appear before the heir to the British throne and
14,500 other people.
   Miss Bumbry sang on the opening night Sunday but couldn't
complete the second act and was replaced by Ghena Dimitrova of
Bulgaria.
   The $2.5 million production of Giuseppe Verdi's music-drama of
ancient Egypt, with a cast of 600, is believed to be the largest
opera staged in Britain.
