<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Spain-Basque     06-29 0196</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Spain-Basque,0202</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspected ETA Member Dies In Jump To Evade Arrest</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RENTERIA, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A suspected member of the Basque
separatist group ETA jumped to his death today shortly after
paramilitary Civil Guard officers came to his apartment to arrest
him, authorities said.
   A statement issued by the Guizpuzcoa province governor's office
said Miguel Arrastia Aguirre, 28, died of severe head injuries
suffered in a jump from a window of an apartment building.
   The statement said Arrastia lowered himself down an internal
shaft of the building when Civil Guard officers came to his
apartment to arrest him.
   Arrastia then climbed back to the top of the building, forced
his way into an apartment and jumped out a fourth-floor window, the
statement said.
   Civil Guard Director Luis Roldan told Spanish National Radio
today that Arrastia was sought in connection with several bombings
in the area carried out on behalf of ETA, which seeks independence
from Spain for the three-province northern Basque region.
   Since taking up arms in 1968, ETA has claimed responsibility for
killing more than 600 people, mainly police, military and Civil
Guard officers.
   ETA stands for homeland and liberty in the Basque language.
</TEXT>
