<HEAD>Robbers Take $92,000 Worth Of Property From Clark Air Base</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Robbers entered four buildings inside
Clark Air Base during the last three days and stole about $92,000
worth of goods, the government-run Philippine News Agency reported
today.
   Thieves first broke into the American base's commissary and the
civil engineering compound Sunday and took $33,000 in foodstuff and
cigarettes, the agency said.
   On Tuesday, robbers struck inside a training center and fled
with aircraft testing equipment and spare parts estimated to cost
$59,000, PNA said.
   Clark police arrested two suspects Tuesday and turned them over
to base authorities, the government news agency. It didn't identify
the suspects.
