<HEAD>Dublin Duck Having Run of Bad Luck</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DUBLIN, Ireland (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Molly, a Dublin duck who in recent years
has sought shelter in the shade of the Irish Parliament building,
had three of her seven day-old ducklings snatched by a magpie on
Wednesday.
   Dessie Rice, a groundskeeper for the government building known
as Leinster House, said Molly was ``not having a lot of luck this
year.''
   Molly, who waddles to Leinster House every spring from her home
in St. Stephen's Green, Dublin's central park, also had a mishap
with a speeding motorist three weeks ago.
   ``I thought at first she was dead,'' said Rice.``But I carried
her back into the grounds and she came to. However, she has been a
little bit lame ever since.''
   In previous years, Molly would lead her young within a few hours
of birth back through the traffic to Stephen's Green where there is
more cover.
   This year, perhaps because of the accident, she ``doesn't seem
inclined to go'' and is still at Leinster House with the four
surviving ducklings, Rice said.
</TEXT>
