<HEAD>Injured Hiker Rescued After Night On Mountain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman who broke her ankle while hiking on
Sleeping Giant Mountain was kept warm overnight by her two dogs
before being rescued 20 hours after her accident, authorities said.
   Helen Kiley, 54, broke her left ankle while trying to stop her
fall part way into a gorge Monday afternoon, Fire Chief John R.
Tramontano said.
   Kiley managed to climb back onto the trail, but was not
discovered by other hikers for about 20 hours, Tramontano said.
   Kiley's two dogs, mongrels with long, shaggy hair, slept close
to her overnight, keeping her warm, the chief said.
   She was admitted to Yale-New Haven Hospital with a broken ankle,
officials there said.
