<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Kenya-Exorcist,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pastor Who Killed Girl In Exorcism Jailed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Contents of following may be objectionable to some readers.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An evangelical pastor was sentenced to
three years in prison for killing a 17-year-old girl while trying
to drive an evil spirit out of her body, the Daily Nation reported
Wednesday.
   John Kimutai Korir, leader of a sect called the Church of God,
denied he tried to murder Jane Chepkemoi, who had escaped from a
mental institution and was the daughter of a church member, the
newspaper said.
   At Korir's trial in the western town of Nakuru, state counsel
Horace Okumu described the exorcism rite:
   ``The churchman asked for a panga (machete knife), cut open
(her) chest and removed the lungs. Korir then placed the lungs in
Jane's mouth, on pretext that he was chasing away the demons.''
   The pastor and his followers then left the girl and continued to
pray for her nearby. When they returned, she was dead.
</TEXT>
