<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Food Aid,0140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Food Aid Announced For Vietnam, Ethiopia, Algeria</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROME (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The World Food Program said Wednesday it will send
$9.1 million in emergency food aid to help about 1.5 million
drought victims in Vietnam.
   The agency also announced it will send $334,720 in food aid to
85,000 Sudanese refugees in Ethiopia and $485,700 in assistance to
help refugees from Niger and Mali living in Algeria.
   Vietnam will receive 29,000 tons of flour for 1.5 million
drought victims and 720 tons of vegetable oil to supplement the
diet of 600,000 children for two months, the agency said.
   Seven million people in northern Vietnam face the possibility of
severe food shortages or famine as a result of dwindling supplies
and poor harvests, according to the United Nations Food and
Agriculture Organization, which approved the emergency aid.
