<HEAD>US, Thailand Plan Joint Military Training Exercise</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The United States and Thailand will stage a
routine joint military training exercise over the next month in two
sections of Thailand, the Pentagon said Wednesday.
   The exercise, code-named ``Cobra Gold 88,'' is the seventh such
exercise in what has become a continuing series. It will be staged
from July 4 to Aug. 3 ``in and around Nakhon Ratchasima (Korat) and
in Rayong Province,'' the Pentagon said in a statement.
   ``The exercise will include an amphibious landing and culminate
in a joint-combined air and land assault,'' the Pentagon added.
   ``Elements of the U.S. Pacific Air Forces, U.S. Pacific Fleet,
U.S. Army Western Command, Strategic Air Command, Military Airlift
Command and Special Operations Command-Pacific will participate in
the exercise. At the conclusion of the exercise, all U.S. forces
will return to their home bases.''
