<HEAD>Cargo Plane Crashes, Five Hurt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A DC-6 plane loaded with frozen
shrimp to the United States crashed shortly after takeoff
Wednesday, injuring four crewmen and the American pilot.
   A spokesman for AESA, the Salvadoran company that owns the
aircraft, said it crashed at 1:13 p.m. (3:13 p.m. EDT), moments
after taking off for Miami from the international airport 21 miles
southeast of the capital.
   The spokesman, who declined to give his name, identifed the
injured pilot as Robert Anderson. He did not know the age or
hometown of the pilot, or the extent of his injuries.
   The spokesman had no information on the condition of the four
crewmen, either. He said all five were taken to a San Salvador
hospital for treatment.
