<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street 11am,0246</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The stock market showed a modest gain today in a
bid to extend Tuesday's rally.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, up 22.41 on Tuesday,
rose 6.22 to 2,137.09 by 11 a.m. today on Wall Street.
   Gainers outnumbered losers by about 4 to 3 in the overall tally
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 647 up, 481 down and
552 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 51.53 million shares at
midmorning.
   Analysts said the market continued to benefit from expectations
of a continuing rally by the dollar in foreign exchange.
   A steady to stronger dollar would presumably attract money from
overseas investors to both stocks and bonds traded in the United
States.
   Worries over upward pressure on commodity prices eased,
meanwhile, after Tuesday's rain in much of the Midwest.
   With all that, brokers said many investors were reluctant to
chase after stocks at levels near the high point of the range in
which they have fluctuated since the crash last fall.
   Gainers among the blue chips included International Business
Machines, up 1 at 128; DuPont, up \ at 90~; Alcoa, up 1 at 53|, and
International Paper, up [ at 47{.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks rose
.34 to 154.11. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up .06 at 308.48.
