<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks, 1st Ld-Writethru, f0034,0240</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Shares Finish Lower</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: RECASTS throughout to UPDATE with later activity; No pickup</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices closed lower Wednesday on the London
Stock Exchange as the market drifted aimlessly in the absence of
news.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index slipped 1.8
points, or 0.1 percent, to close at 1,855.1, the session's low.
   Volume was a slim 378.0 million shares, down from 386.7 million
shares traded Tuesday.
   Dealers said the market appeared to be consolidating around the
1,850 to 1,860 level. The small range in which the FT-SE 100-index
moved Wednesday reflected the market's indecision about which
direction to take next.
   ``We're in limbo,'' said Jeremy Evans, an equity market
strategist at County NatWest WoodMac.
   Evans said activity in the market likely would be limited until
it sees another half-percentage-point rise in the base lending
rate, following the half-point hike to 9.5 percent on Tuesday.
   ``Once we get that out of the way, we'll be able to move out of
the range,'' he said.
   Several dealers said the market also might remain quiet
following the end of the earnings reporting season.
   ``Without a steady stream of results to motivate things down
here, it's going to be awfully quiet,'' one equity salesman said.
   Another dealer said activity likely would remain subdued until
the next set of U.S. trade figures, slated for release in mid-July.
</TEXT>
